 Nigerian attacking midfielder Wisdom Kanu won two major awards in Slovakia after signed off on the season on a high note. The 27-year-old former Lagos Islanders emerged the highest goal scorer in Slovakia’s second-tier league with Slavoj Trebisov after banging 18 goals in 27 appearances. Kanu named Best Discovery of the Year and make the Team of the Season in Slovakia’s second division. Kanu started his career with Lagos Island before a spell abroad at Spisska Nova Ves, Inter Bratislava, Zlate Moravce, Vranov and Poprad. Post Views: 
